description:
Origin

Weirdworld was a world full of fantasy that was the home of Tyndall and Velenna.

Creation

Weirdworld is a fantasy series created by Doug Moench and Mike Ploog for Marvel Comics, set in a magical dimension. It first appeared in Marvel Super Action issue 1 (1976). The concept was portrayed in a number of Marvel Comics, such as Marvel Fanfare and the Epic series.

Major Story Arcs

Secret Wars and Beyond

In 2015, Marvel would publish a new Weirdworld series as part of the Secret Wars event, setting Arkon from Avengers and X-Men fame into Weirdworld. Other residents of Weirdworld where Crystar, Warbow, Jennifer Kale, Morgan le Fay and Skull the Slayer

In the Marvel Universe.

After the events of Secret Wars, a part of Weirdworld was moved to the main universe, located somewhere in the Bermuda Triangle. It was revealed that Black Knight had been transported into Weirdworld. Others that remain in the real are Arkon, Becca Rodriguez, Crystar Crystal Warrior and Morgan le Fay.

deck: A large manor that once belonged to the psychologically tormented and disturbed Decaster family. It is now home to the ghostly remnants of the Decaster's.
description:
Overview

The Decaster House was once home to a family known only as the Decasters; a psychologically tormented and rather disturbed family. The head of the house, Lionel Decaster, wasn't known for being sane or sociable, and kept his family locked inside the house as prisoners, never letting them step outside for any reason. Due to this rule, many of the Decaster children resulted to reproducing with other family members, one of the many sick and twisted happens that took place within it's confines. Eventually, one of Lionel's granddaughters had enough and slit his throat with a razor, killing him.

The loss of the Decaster leader and the psychological trauma the other family members had endured over the previous years resulted in them staying inside the house, cannibalizing other family members until the final one starved.

The Decaster house then became home to the resting place of Samuel Loom, a thief who was attempting to hide the Matheson Collection of 17th Century coins which he had stolen. Due to the age of the house and it's ruinous state, a large wooden beam fell on him and prevented him from moving, thus he died of starvation.

The Goon and Franky also ventured to the Decaster house in search of the coin collection. During their time within the manor they encountered the spirits of the Decaster family. Thankfully, The Goon had been given a magical artifact allowing him to defeat the Decaster's and claim the coin collection.
name: Decaster House

deck: The home and workplace for Brianna Von Zeigler (Astro-Bunny) who happens to be a part-time exotic dancer. The Golden Moon is a nexus for many outpost worlds where various races and species all come to have a good time. This is s mini world catering to all.
description: The Golden Moon Casino-Space Station is often referred as a galactic hub where the various worlds and dimensions meet. Many alien races come to gamble, enjoy the food and games, and in the upper level, enjoy adult entertainment. One of the main attractions is Brianna Von Zeigler, also known as Astro-Bunny. This is where she resides and works, often using the Moon as a neutral meeting place and as a source of information. The Moon caters to individual tastes as well as a tourist trap for families.
